  "informal_statement": "The sum of squares of the first n+1 Fibonacci numbers (fib 0 through fib n) equals fib(n) * fib(n+1).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Induction on n. Base case n=0: both sides are 0. Inductive step: expand the sum via Finset.sum_range_succ, substitute the inductive hypothesis, then rewrite fib(n+2) via the Fibonacci recurrence Nat.fib_add_two to factor fib(n)*fib(n+1) + fib(n+1)^2 = fib(n+1)*(fib(n)+fib(n+1)) = fib(n+1)*fib(n+2), closed by ring.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem sum_fib_sq (n : ℕ) : (∑ i ∈ Finset.range (n + 1), (Nat.fib i) ^ 2) = Nat.fib n * Nat.fib (n + 1)",
